&gt; The [concat() method is used to merge two or more arrays](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/concat). This method does not change the existing arrays, but instead __returns a new array__.

So, `obj.concat(k)` doesn&#39;t do anything, and you&#39;re returning an _unchanged_ `obj` in the next line.

To solve this you can assign the concat to a new variable and return that...

    const newObj = obj.concat(k);
    return newObj;

... or simply return the result of the concat:

    return obj.concat(k);

